  "commentary": "**DEALER HEDGING COMMENTARY:**\n\nWith SPX at 6998.11 sitting just below the massive 7000 gamma wall (18.8B), dealers are positioned to aggressively sell any push above this level as they hedge their long gamma exposure. The PIN regime confirms dealers will provide liquidity by selling rallies and buying dips, creating strong mean-reversion dynamics around current levels. Key resistance stacks up at 7000/7025/7050 with the 6875 flip level providing critical support - a break below shifts dealers to net short gamma and amplifies downside momentum.\n\n**Bottom line:** expect heavy selling pressure on any move above 7000 with choppy action until a clear break of key levels.",
